OL,4,Cpolice officer's face
OL,6,FChief Inspector Iain Wyke said: "The
OL,7,Fpolice officer suffered a deep cut to
OL,8,Fhis upper lip and was shaken by the
OL,9,Fincident.
OL,11,F"He was on duty to ensure that all
OL,12,Fmatch-goers were able to enjoy the
OL,13,Fgame safely so to be assaulted in such
OL,14,Fa manner when he was simply doing his
OL,15,Fjob is shocking.
OL,17,F"Our police officers understand the
OL,18,Frisks of the job, but they should
OL,19,Fnever have to tolerate violence
OL,20,Fagainst them when they are simply
OL,21,Fattempting to carry out their duties.
